events.title: Putting Google Cloud together: querying App Engine logs with BigQuery
events.abstract:
This session will show you how to use multiple Google Technologies together in order to automate import and query your App Engine logs from Big Query including:
- Using the Map Reduce API and the new Log API to read your App Engine logs
- Store your logs into Google Storage using robot account
- Import your logs into Big Query and query them from the web interface or programmatically.

events.title: Advanced HTML Page Authoring Using Modern CSS Features
events.abstract: In this code lab, we'll explore new CSS3 features and show you how to use them, to build amazing HTML pages and web applications. For example, we'll cover CSS3 flexbox, CSS3 multi column and many other features. We'll also review CSS features that make web pages more compelling e.g via using filters.

events.title: Connecting the Developer Cloud to Google Apps
events.abstract: You've got tons of valuable data in App Engine, Google Cloud SQL and Big Query. Your organization runs Google Apps. Here's how to use Google's tools to automate the flow of insights between developers and decision-makers.
events.tags: BigQuery,Fusion Tables,Google Cloud SQL,Google Cloud Storage,Google Apps Script

events.title: Integrate Web Intents into Your Application Today
events.abstract: Web Intents is the future of inter-application communication. In this Code Lab the creators of Web Intents will give you one on one advice about how to integrate Web Intents into your application.

events.title: Building Google+ Hangout Apps
events.abstract: Roll up your sleeves and learn how to build and publish Hangout Apps. Using the Google+ Hangouts API, develop and publish fun & functional Hangout Apps. Walk away with the tools needed to turn your own ideas into awesome Hangout Apps.

events.title: Bullseye : Your First Dart App
events.abstract: Build your first Dart app! We'll lead you through the process of building a modern web app with the Dart platform. You'll leave this session with a working Dart app that works in all modern browsers.

events.title: YouTube API v3
events.abstract: The YouTube Data API is changing, and we're ready to give a first look at the new infrastructure. We'll go into more details about the backend infrastructure powering the new API, as well as the new, modern libraries that will power the next generation of client code.

events.title: Building Web applications in JavaScript that use Google APIs
events.abstract: In this session, you will learn how to use the features of the JavaScript client for Google APIs to build rich web applications. Some of the features we will demonstrate include authentication and CORS.

events.title: YouTube Android Player API
events.abstract: The brand new Android YouTube Player API is here! If you are building Android smartphone, tablet or Google TV applications and want to incorporate high-quality YouTube video playback in your product this session will rock your world.
